                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52UGW_",
                    "body": "It might also we worth adding the following lemma whilst we're at it!\r\n```suggestion\r\n\r\ntheorem ContinouousOn_union_isOpen_iff {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]\r\n    {s t : Set X} (hs : IsOpen s) (ht : IsOpen t) {f : X → Y} :\r\n    ContinuousOn f (s ∪ t) ↔ ContinuousOn f s ∧ ContinuousOn f t :=\r\n  ⟨fun hf ↦ continuousOn_of_union hf, fun ⟨hfs, hft⟩ ↦ hfs.union_isOpen hs ht hft⟩\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T12:31:23Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "Paul-Lez"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52UOhi",
                    "body": "ContinuousOn.union_isOpen should be called `ContinuousOn.union_of_isOpen` - since `isOpen` is one of the hypotheses.",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T12:51:45Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "grunweg"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52UO3b",
                    "body": "And I believe most other files would name the new lemma `continouousOn_union_isOpen`",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T12:52:46Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "grunweg"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52UHDo",
                    "body": "Small nitpick: this file already has `α β` as topological spaces, so I think it would be cleaner to use those variables \r\n(and perhaps `ContinuousOn.union_continuousAt` and `ContinuousOn.union_isClosed` should also be changed in a similar manner)",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T12:33:53Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "Paul-Lez"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52UN-w",
                    "body": "*If* you care about using Greek letters, you should file a preliminary PR renaming all the occurrences in the file. (I would certainly review such a PR.)",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T12:50:03Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "grunweg"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52U1ZR",
                    "body": "Done in #22691 (just to clarify, my intention wasn't to suggest that these results *should* be stated with Greek letters, but rather that it might be nicer to stay consistent with the notation of (the majority of) the file)",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T14:41:39Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "Paul-Lez"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52VF73",
                    "body": "I would say they should use Roman letters (usually) - but also that changing all files manually is a lot of work that might not be the best use of one's time.",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T15:13:04Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "grunweg"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52VKrN",
                    "body": "That sounds reasonable - good to know:)",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T15:25:22Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "Paul-Lez"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c52UOWF",
                    "body": "It's a bit unusual to have a theorem whose conclusion is a conjunction of statements. Usually, one would have separate statements for each.",
                    "createdAt": "2025-03-07T12:51:09Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "grunweg"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
